The Vice President expressed his condolences on the passing of Lee Kuan Yew, the founding father of Singapore. He praised Lee's leadership and his role in Singapore's economic growth, making it one of the most prosperous countries in the world. The Vice President admired Lee's commitment to excellence in public service and valued his insights on Asia, geopolitics, and economics. He also mentioned that Lee believed in the importance of America's role in the Pacific region and considered him a friend and admirer of the United States. The Vice President offered his condolences to Lee's family and joined the people of Singapore in mourning his loss.